I hope your grandmother feels better, Carnage. When I rule the world I'll 
abolish death or something (unless, of course, for those rebellious fools who 
will dare to stand up to me).

About the messed up order email things, I've also been getting my emails in 
funny order. If anyone else is experiencing this problem, you can go to the 
site (http://nbwrpg.tripod.com) and click on 'messages', or just go to 
http://egroups.com/messages/nbwrpg. The messages will be in order there.

::Prowl::

Prowl's eyes widen as Iron Raptor sets his broken wing, sending a jolt of 
pain through his systems, the fact that she was leaning on his broken ribs 
not helping too much to relieve it. He grins rather painfully at her joke, 
being too damaged and worn-out to think of a reply.

Prowl nods as Iron Raptor suggests to get repaired, taking a few steps as she 
tugs on his hand, and falling to his knees in pain as his broken ribs rub 
against each other. Shakily, he stands up, using Iron Raptor for support and 
holding his side with his other hand.

"Yeah, let's get to the CR chamber," he says through clenched teeth (due to 
pain) to Iron Raptor, turning to look at Octociz.

"We'll be ok," he says to the new maximal, "Go see if any of the others need 
help."

His optics widen as he hears an explosion behind him, spinning around quickly 
and ignoring the pain in his side to see Nemesis' missile hit the rock he had 
been leaning on moments earlier. He looks up at the sky to see the alliance 
member leaving.

Prowl looks back at Iron Raptor.

"Yeah, let's go."
